        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Vishwajyot School - Kharghar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Tanvi Dabholkar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-06-21",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "First would like to specify that this review is based upon my experience and a few of our friends. We took admission of our child in pre primary considering that now my child should get the exposure of a big school. Liked the infrastructure so paid the fees. 22-23 year has been the worst for my child. She didn’t learn anything. We were attracted for their unique teaching methods. But for a year all my daughter did was paint and made craft and god knows what. No worksheets were given to us for homework. We didn’t know where my daughter stood in terms of academics. She had already learnt a lot in her previous school which was wasted in this one year. Trying not to interrupt with Vishwajyot’s teaching I didn’t taught her at home. A few cases from primary grades. First hand experiences shared by parents with me were worst too. No writing done at all. No communication sent to parents. No coordination between the staff, teachers, management etc. Other than this the management is pathetic. The receptionist doesn’t know to smile or even greet. We withdrew the admission and along with us two other parents did. We got TC - leaving certificate photo on a black and white paper on email after 2 months of follow up. We got our caution money refund after almost 100 days of harassment and warnings. We are happy with the withdrawal of our child from this school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Vishwajyot School - Kharghar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Anitha Srivat"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-05-01",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "We had a great experience in Vishwajyot for my daughter's pre-primary classes. Their innovative teaching methods, the individual attention of the teachers and the class environment needs a special mention. My daughter used to look forward to go to school everyday. The community lunch system helps a great way in independent eating and sharing among kids. The kids are never judged with exams and grades. Each kid's strengths and weakness are identified and addressed through periodic assessments.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
